name: sqladmin
title: Cloud SQL Administration API
description: Creates and configures Cloud SQL instances, which provide fully-managed MySQL databases.

parameters.name: userIp
parameters.desc: IP address of the site where the request originates. Use this if you want to enforce per-user limits.

parameters.name: fields
parameters.desc: Selector specifying which fields to include in a partial response.

parameters.name: key
parameters.desc: API key. Your API key identifies your project and provides you with API access, quota, and reports. Required unless you provide an OAuth 2.0 token.

parameters.name: oauth_token
parameters.desc: OAuth 2.0 token for the current user.

parameters.name: prettyPrint
parameters.desc: Returns response with indentations and line breaks.

parameters.name: quotaUser
parameters.desc: Available to use for quota purposes for server-side applications. Can be any arbitrary string assigned to a user, but should not exceed 40 characters. Overrides userIp if both are provided.

fields.name: items
fields.desc: List of database resources in the instance.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#databasesList.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#failoverContext.

fields.name: settingsVersion
fields.desc: The current settings version of this instance. Request will be rejected if this version doesn't match the current settings version.

schemas.name: MySqlReplicaConfiguration
schemas.desc: Read-replica configuration specific to MySQL databases.

fields.name: masterHeartbeatPeriod
fields.desc: Interval in milliseconds between replication heartbeats.

fields.name: verifyServerCertificate
fields.desc: Whether or not to check the master's Common Name value in the certificate that it sends during the SSL handshake.

fields.name: clientCertificate
fields.desc: PEM representation of the slave's x509 certificate.

fields.name: clientKey
fields.desc: PEM representation of the slave's private key. The corresponsing public key is encoded in the client's certificate.

fields.name: connectRetryInterval
fields.desc: Seconds to wait between connect retries. MySQL's default is 60 seconds.

fields.name: password
fields.desc: The password for the replication connection.

fields.name: sslCipher
fields.desc: A list of permissible ciphers to use for SSL encryption.

fields.name: username
fields.desc: The username for the replication connection.

fields.name: caCertificate
fields.desc: PEM representation of the trusted CA's x509 certificate.

fields.name: dumpFilePath
fields.desc: Path to a SQL dump file in Google Cloud Storage from which the slave instance is to be created. The URI is in the form gs://bucketName/fileName. Compressed gzip files (.gz) are also supported. Dumps should have the binlog co-ordinates from which replication should begin. This can be accomplished by setting --master-data to 1 when using mysqldump.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#mysqlReplicaConfiguration.

fields.name: public_key
fields.desc: PEM encoded public key to include in the signed certificate.

schemas.name: Database
schemas.desc: A database resource inside a Cloud SQL instance.

fields.name: project
fields.desc: The project ID of the project containing the Cloud SQL database. The Google apps domain is prefixed if applicable.

fields.name: selfLink
fields.desc: The URI of this resource.

fields.name: charset
fields.desc: The MySQL charset value.

fields.name: collation
fields.desc: The MySQL collation value.

fields.name: etag
fields.desc: HTTP 1.1 Entity tag for the resource.

fields.name: instance
fields.desc: The name of the Cloud SQL instance. This does not include the project ID.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#database.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: The name of the database in the Cloud SQL instance. This does not include the project ID or instance name.

schemas.name: Labels
schemas.desc: User defined labels for Cloud SQL instances.

fields.name: key
fields.desc: The key of the label.

fields.name: value
fields.desc: The value of the label.

schemas.name: ReplicaConfiguration
schemas.desc: Read-replica configuration for connecting to the master.

fields.name: failoverTarget
fields.desc:
Specifies if the replica is the failover target. If the field is set to true the replica will be designated as a failover replica. In case the master instance fails, the replica instance will be promoted as the new master instance.
Only one replica can be specified as failover target, and the replica has to be in different zone with the master instance.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#replicaConfiguration.

fields.name: mysqlReplicaConfiguration
fields.desc: MySQL specific configuration when replicating from a MySQL on-premises master. Replication configuration information such as the username, password, certificates, and keys are not stored in the instance metadata. The configuration information is used only to set up the replication connection and is stored by MySQL in a file named master.info in the data directory.

fields.name: sha1Fingerprint
fields.desc: Sha1 Fingerprint.

fields.name: cert
fields.desc: PEM representation.

fields.name: commonName
fields.desc: User supplied name. Constrained to [a-zA-Z.-_ ]+.

fields.name: expirationTime
fields.desc: The time when the certificate expires in RFC 3339 format, for example 2012-11-15T16:19:00.094Z.

fields.name: instance
fields.desc: Name of the database instance.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#sslCert.

fields.name: selfLink
fields.desc: The URI of this resource.

fields.name: certSerialNumber
fields.desc: Serial number, as extracted from the certificate.

fields.name: createTime
fields.desc: The time when the certificate was created in RFC 3339 format, for example 2012-11-15T16:19:00.094Z

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#truncateLogContext.

fields.name: logType
fields.desc: The type of log to truncate. Valid values are MYSQL_GENERAL_TABLE and MYSQL_SLOW_TABLE.

fields.name: exportContext
fields.desc: Contains details about the export operation.

fields.name: restoreBackupContext
fields.desc: Parameters required to perform the restore backup operation.

fields.name: ipAddress
fields.desc: The IP address assigned.

fields.name: timeToRetire
fields.desc: The due time for this IP to be retired in RFC 3339 format, for example 2012-11-15T16:19:00.094Z. This field is only available when the IP is scheduled to be retired.

fields.name: type
fields.desc: The type of this IP address. A PRIMARY address is an address that can accept incoming connections. An OUTGOING address is the source address of connections originating from the instance, if supported.

fields.name: hostPort
fields.desc: The host and port of the on-premises instance in host:port format

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#onPremisesConfiguration.

schemas.name: Tier
schemas.desc: A Google Cloud SQL service tier resource.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#tier.

fields.name: region
fields.desc: The applicable regions for this tier.

fields.name: tier
fields.desc: An identifier for the service tier, for example D1, D2 etc. For related information, see Pricing.

fields.name: DiskQuota
fields.desc: The maximum disk size of this tier in bytes.

fields.name: RAM
fields.desc: The maximum RAM usage of this tier in bytes.

fields.name: connectionName
fields.desc: Connection name of the Cloud SQL instance used in connection strings.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#instance.

fields.name: masterInstanceName
fields.desc: The name of the instance which will act as master in the replication setup.

fields.name: suspensionReason
fields.desc: If the instance state is SUSPENDED, the reason for the suspension.

fields.name: state
fields.desc:
The current serving state of the Cloud SQL instance. This can be one of the following.
RUNNABLE: The instance is running, or is ready to run when accessed.
SUSPENDED: The instance is not available, for example due to problems with billing.
PENDING_CREATE: The instance is being created.
MAINTENANCE: The instance is down for maintenance.
FAILED: The instance creation failed.
UNKNOWN_STATE: The state of the instance is unknown.

fields.name: backendType
fields.desc:
FIRST_GEN: Basic Cloud SQL instance that runs in a Google-managed container.
SECOND_GEN: A newer Cloud SQL backend that runs in a Compute Engine VM.
EXTERNAL: A MySQL server that is not managed by Google.

fields.name: etag
fields.desc: HTTP 1.1 Entity tag for the resource.

fields.name: instanceType
fields.desc:
The instance type. This can be one of the following.
CLOUD_SQL_INSTANCE: A Cloud SQL instance that is not replicating from a master.
ON_PREMISES_INSTANCE: An instance running on the customer's premises.
READ_REPLICA_INSTANCE: A Cloud SQL instance configured as a read-replica.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: Name of the Cloud SQL instance. This does not include the project ID.

fields.name: serverCaCert
fields.desc: SSL configuration.

fields.name: serviceAccountEmailAddress
fields.desc: The service account email address assigned to the instance. This property is applicable only to Second Generation instances.

fields.name: databaseVersion
fields.desc: The database engine type and version. The databaseVersion can not be changed after instance creation. Can be MYSQL_5_5, MYSQL_5_6 or MYSQL_5_7. Defaults to MYSQL_5_6. MYSQL_5_7 is applicable only to Second Generation instances.

fields.name: maxDiskSize
fields.desc: The maximum disk size of the instance in bytes.

fields.name: project
fields.desc: The project ID of the project containing the Cloud SQL instance. The Google apps domain is prefixed if applicable.

fields.name: replicaConfiguration
fields.desc: Configuration specific to read-replicas replicating from on-premises masters.

fields.name: settings
fields.desc: The user settings.

fields.name: replicaNames
fields.desc: The replicas of the instance.

fields.name: selfLink
fields.desc: The URI of this resource.

fields.name: currentDiskSize
fields.desc: The current disk usage of the instance in bytes. This property has been deprecated. Users should use the "cloudsql.googleapis.com/database/disk/bytes_used" metric in Cloud Monitoring API instead. Please see https://groups.google.com/d/msg/google-cloud-sql-announce/I_7-F9EBhT0/BtvFtdFeAgAJ for details.

fields.name: failoverReplica
fields.desc: The name and status of the failover replica. This property is applicable only to Second Generation instances.

fields.name: available
fields.desc: The availability status of the failover replica. A false status indicates that the failover replica is out of sync. The master can only failover to the falover replica when the status is true.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: The name of the failover replica. If specified at instance creation, a failover replica is created for the instance. The name doesn't include the project ID. This property is applicable only to Second Generation instances.

fields.name: ipAddresses
fields.desc: The assigned IP addresses for the instance.

fields.name: ipv6Address
fields.desc: The IPv6 address assigned to the instance. This property is applicable only to First Generation instances.

fields.name: onPremisesConfiguration
fields.desc: Configuration specific to on-premises instances.

fields.name: region
fields.desc: The geographical region. Can be us-central (FIRST_GEN instances only), us-central1 (SECOND_GEN instances only), asia-east1 or europe-west1. Defaults to us-central or us-central1 depending on the instance type (First Generation or Second Generation). The region can not be changed after instance creation.

fields.name: items
fields.desc: List of flags.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#flagsList.

fields.name: importContext
fields.desc: Contains details about the import operation.

fields.name: truncateLogContext
fields.desc: Contains details about the truncate log operation.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#sslCertsList.

fields.name: items
fields.desc: List of client certificates for the instance.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#backupConfiguration.

fields.name: startTime
fields.desc: Start time for the daily backup configuration in UTC timezone in the 24 hour format - HH:MM.

fields.name: binaryLogEnabled
fields.desc: Whether binary log is enabled. If backup configuration is disabled, binary log must be disabled as well.

fields.name: enabled
fields.desc: Whether this configuration is enabled.

fields.name: failoverContext
fields.desc: Failover Context.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#operationError.

fields.name: message
fields.desc: Additional information about the error encountered.

fields.name: code
fields.desc: Identifies the specific error that occurred.

schemas.name: OperationErrors
schemas.desc: Database instance operation errors list wrapper.

fields.name: errors
fields.desc: The list of errors encountered while processing this operation.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#operationErrors.

fields.name: items
fields.desc: List of operation resources.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#operationsList.

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc: The continuation token, used to page through large result sets. Provide this value in a subsequent request to return the next page of results.

schemas.name: BackupRun
schemas.desc: A database instance backup run resource.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#backupRun.

fields.name: selfLink
fields.desc: The URI of this resource.

fields.name: startTime
fields.desc: The time the backup operation actually started in UTC timezone in RFC 3339 format, for example 2012-11-15T16:19:00.094Z.

fields.name: status
fields.desc: The status of this run.

fields.name: type
fields.desc: The type of this run; can be either "AUTOMATED" or "ON_DEMAND".

fields.name: endTime
fields.desc: The time the backup operation completed in UTC timezone in RFC 3339 format, for example 2012-11-15T16:19:00.094Z.

fields.name: enqueuedTime
fields.desc: The time the run was enqueued in UTC timezone in RFC 3339 format, for example 2012-11-15T16:19:00.094Z.

fields.name: error
fields.desc: Information about why the backup operation failed. This is only present if the run has the FAILED status.

fields.name: windowStartTime
fields.desc: The start time of the backup window during which this the backup was attempted in RFC 3339 format, for example 2012-11-15T16:19:00.094Z.

fields.name: description
fields.desc: The description of this run, only applicable to on-demand backups.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: A unique identifier for this backup run. Note that this is unique only within the scope of a particular Cloud SQL instance.

fields.name: instance
fields.desc: Name of the database instance.

schemas.name: DatabaseFlags
schemas.desc: MySQL flags for Cloud SQL instances.

fields.name: value
fields.desc: The value of the flag. Booleans should be set to on for true and off for false. This field must be omitted if the flag doesn't take a value.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: The name of the flag. These flags are passed at instance startup, so include both MySQL server options and MySQL system variables. Flags should be specified with underscores, not hyphens. For more information, see Configuring MySQL Flags in the Google Cloud SQL documentation, as well as the official MySQL documentation for server options and system variables.

fields.name: csvImportOptions
fields.desc: Options for importing data as CSV.

fields.name: columns
fields.desc: The columns to which CSV data is imported. If not specified, all columns of the database table are loaded with CSV data.

fields.name: table
fields.desc: The table to which CSV data is imported.

fields.name: database
fields.desc: The database (for example, guestbook) to which the import is made. If fileType is SQL and no database is specified, it is assumed that the database is specified in the file to be imported. If fileType is CSV, it must be specified.

fields.name: fileType
fields.desc:
The file type for the specified uri.
SQL: The file contains SQL statements.
CSV: The file contains CSV data.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#importContext.

fields.name: uri
fields.desc: A path to the file in Google Cloud Storage from which the import is made. The URI is in the form gs://bucketName/fileName. Compressed gzip files (.gz) are supported when fileType is SQL.

fields.name: authorizedNetworks
fields.desc: The list of external networks that are allowed to connect to the instance using the IP. In CIDR notation, also known as 'slash' notation (e.g. 192.168.100.0/24).

fields.name: ipv4Enabled
fields.desc: Whether the instance should be assigned an IP address or not.

fields.name: requireSsl
fields.desc: Whether the mysqld should default to 'REQUIRE X509' for users connecting over IP.

schemas.name: MaintenanceWindow
schemas.desc: Maintenance window. This specifies when a v2 Cloud SQL instance should preferably be restarted for system maintenance puruposes.

fields.name: day
fields.desc: day of week (1-7), starting on Monday.

fields.name: hour
fields.desc: hour of day - 0 to 23.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#maintenanceWindow.

fields.name: certInfo
fields.desc: The public information about the cert.

fields.name: certPrivateKey
fields.desc: The private key for the client cert, in pem format. Keep private in order to protect your security.

fields.name: items
fields.desc: List of tiers.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#tiersList.

fields.name: binLogCoordinates
fields.desc: Binary log coordinates, if specified, indentify the the position up to which the source instance should be cloned. If not specified, the source instance is cloned up to the most recent binary log coordintes.

fields.name: destinationInstanceName
fields.desc: Name of the Cloud SQL instance to be created as a clone.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#cloneContext.

fields.name: items
fields.desc: A list of backup runs in reverse chronological order of the enqueued time.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#backupRunsList.

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc: The continuation token, used to page through large result sets. Provide this value in a subsequent request to return the next page of results.

fields.name: csvExportOptions
fields.desc: Options for exporting data as CSV.

fields.name: selectQuery
fields.desc: The select query used to extract the data.

fields.name: databases
fields.desc: Databases (for example, guestbook) from which the export is made. If fileType is SQL and no database is specified, all databases are exported. If fileType is CSV, you can optionally specify at most one database to export. If csvExportOptions.selectQuery also specifies the database, this field will be ignored.

fields.name: fileType
fields.desc:
The file type for the specified uri.
SQL: The file contains SQL statements.
CSV: The file contains CSV data.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#exportContext.

fields.name: sqlExportOptions
fields.desc: Options for exporting data as SQL statements.

fields.name: schemaOnly
fields.desc: Export only schemas.

fields.name: tables
fields.desc: Tables to export, or that were exported, from the specified database. If you specify tables, specify one and only one database.

fields.name: uri
fields.desc: The path to the file in Google Cloud Storage where the export will be stored. The URI is in the form gs://bucketName/fileName. If the file already exists, the operation fails. If fileType is SQL and the filename ends with .gz, the contents are compressed.

schemas.name: Flag
schemas.desc: A Google Cloud SQL service flag resource.

fields.name: appliesTo
fields.desc: The database version this flag applies to. Can be MYSQL_5_5, MYSQL_5_6, or MYSQL_5_7. MYSQL_5_7 is applicable only to Second Generation instances.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#flag.

fields.name: maxValue
fields.desc: For INTEGER flags, the maximum allowed value.

fields.name: minValue
fields.desc: For INTEGER flags, the minimum allowed value.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: This is the name of the flag. Flag names always use underscores, not hyphens, e.g. max_allowed_packet

fields.name: requiresRestart
fields.desc: Indicates whether changing this flag will trigger a database restart. Only applicable to Second Generation instances.

fields.name: type
fields.desc: The type of the flag. Flags are typed to being BOOLEAN, STRING, INTEGER or NONE. NONE is used for flags which do not take a value, such as skip_grant_tables.

fields.name: allowedStringValues
fields.desc: For STRING flags, a list of strings that the value can be set to.

fields.name: items
fields.desc: List of database instance resources.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#instancesList.

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc: The continuation token, used to page through large result sets. Provide this value in a subsequent request to return the next page of results.

schemas.name: LocationPreference
schemas.desc: Preferred location. This specifies where a Cloud SQL instance should preferably be located, either in a specific Compute Engine zone, or co-located with an App Engine application. Note that if the preferred location is not available, the instance will be located as close as possible within the region. Only one location may be specified.

fields.name: followGaeApplication
fields.desc: The AppEngine application to follow, it must be in the same region as the Cloud SQL instance.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#locationPreference.

fields.name: zone
fields.desc: The preferred Compute Engine zone (e.g. us-centra1-a, us-central1-b, etc.).

schemas.name: RestoreBackupContext
schemas.desc: Database instance restore from backup context.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#restoreBackupContext.

fields.name: backupRunId
fields.desc: The ID of the backup run to restore from.

fields.name: instanceId
fields.desc: The ID of the instance that the backup was taken from.

fields.name: serverCaCert
fields.desc: The server Certificate Authority's certificate. If this is missing you can force a new one to be generated by calling resetSslConfig method on instances resource.

fields.name: clientCert
fields.desc: The new client certificate and private key. The new certificate will not work until the instance is restarted for First Generation instances.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#sslCertsInsert.

fields.name: operation
fields.desc: The operation to track the ssl certs insert request.

schemas.name: AclEntry
schemas.desc: An entry for an Access Control list.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#aclEntry.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: An optional label to identify this entry.

fields.name: value
fields.desc: The whitelisted value for the access control list.

fields.name: expirationTime
fields.desc: The time when this access control entry expires in RFC 3339 format, for example 2012-11-15T16:19:00.094Z.

fields.name: password
fields.desc: The password for the user.

fields.name: project
fields.desc: The project ID of the project containing the Cloud SQL database. The Google apps domain is prefixed if applicable. Can be omitted for update since it is already specified on the URL.

fields.name: etag
fields.desc: HTTP 1.1 Entity tag for the resource.

fields.name: host
fields.desc: The host name from which the user can connect. For insert operations, host defaults to an empty string. For update operations, host is specified as part of the request URL. The host name cannot be updated after insertion.

fields.name: instance
fields.desc: The name of the Cloud SQL instance. This does not include the project ID. Can be omitted for update since it is already specified on the URL.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#user.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: The name of the user in the Cloud SQL instance. Can be omitted for update since it is already specified on the URL.

fields.name: cloneContext
fields.desc: Contains details about the clone operation.

schemas.name: Operation
schemas.desc: An Operations resource contains information about database instance operations such as create, delete, and restart. Operations resources are created in response to operations that were initiated; you never create them directly.

fields.name: user
fields.desc: The email address of the user who initiated this operation.

fields.name: exportContext
fields.desc: The context for export operation, if applicable.

fields.name: importContext
fields.desc: The context for import operation, if applicable.

fields.name: insertTime
fields.desc: The time this operation was enqueued in UTC timezone in RFC 3339 format, for example 2012-11-15T16:19:00.094Z.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: An identifier that uniquely identifies the operation. You can use this identifier to retrieve the Operations resource that has information about the operation.

fields.name: targetId
fields.desc: Name of the database instance related to this operation.

fields.name: endTime
fields.desc: The time this operation finished in UTC timezone in RFC 3339 format, for example 2012-11-15T16:19:00.094Z.

fields.name: operationType
fields.desc: The type of the operation. Valid values are CREATE, DELETE, UPDATE, RESTART, IMPORT, EXPORT, BACKUP_VOLUME, RESTORE_VOLUME, CREATE_USER, DELETE_USER, CREATE_DATABASE, DELETE_DATABASE .

fields.name: targetProject
fields.desc: The project ID of the target instance related to this operation.

fields.name: error
fields.desc: If errors occurred during processing of this operation, this field will be populated.

fields.name: selfLink
fields.desc: The URI of this resource.

fields.name: startTime
fields.desc: The time this operation actually started in UTC timezone in RFC 3339 format, for example 2012-11-15T16:19:00.094Z.

fields.name: status
fields.desc: The status of an operation. Valid values are PENDING, RUNNING, DONE, UNKNOWN.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#operation.

fields.name: targetLink
fields.desc: The URI of the instance related to the operation.

fields.name: dataDiskType
fields.desc: The type of data disk. Only supported for Second Generation instances. The default type is PD_SSD. Applies only to Second Generation instances.

fields.name: databaseReplicationEnabled
fields.desc: Configuration specific to read replica instances. Indicates whether replication is enabled or not.

fields.name: storageAutoResizeLimit
fields.desc: The maximum size to which storage capacity can be automatically increased. The default value is 0, which specifies that there is no limit. Applies only to Second Generation instances.

fields.name: authorizedGaeApplications
fields.desc: The App Engine app IDs that can access this instance. This property is only applicable to First Generation instances.

fields.name: databaseFlags
fields.desc: The database flags passed to the instance at startup.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#settings.

fields.name: locationPreference
fields.desc: The location preference settings. This allows the instance to be located as near as possible to either an App Engine app or GCE zone for better performance. App Engine co-location is only applicable to First Generation instances.

fields.name: pricingPlan
fields.desc: The pricing plan for this instance. This can be either PER_USE or PACKAGE. Only PER_USE is supported for Second Generation instances.

fields.name: settingsVersion
fields.desc: The version of instance settings. This is a required field for update method to make sure concurrent updates are handled properly. During update, use the most recent settingsVersion value for this instance and do not try to update this value.

fields.name: availabilityType
fields.desc: Reserved for future use.

fields.name: dataDiskSizeGb
fields.desc: The size of data disk, in GB. The data disk size minimum is 10GB. Applies only to Second Generation instances.

fields.name: ipConfiguration
fields.desc: The settings for IP Management. This allows to enable or disable the instance IP and manage which external networks can connect to the instance. The IPv4 address cannot be disabled for Second Generation instances.

fields.name: labels
fields.desc: User defined labels.

fields.name: replicationType
fields.desc: The type of replication this instance uses. This can be either ASYNCHRONOUS or SYNCHRONOUS. This property is only applicable to First Generation instances.

fields.name: storageAutoResize
fields.desc: Configuration to increase storage size automatically. The default value is false. Applies only to Second Generation instances.

fields.name: backupConfiguration
fields.desc: The daily backup configuration for the instance.

fields.name: crashSafeReplicationEnabled
fields.desc: Configuration specific to read replica instances. Indicates whether database flags for crash-safe replication are enabled. This property is only applicable to First Generation instances.

fields.name: maintenanceWindow
fields.desc: The maintenance window for this instance. This specifies when the instance may be restarted for maintenance purposes. Applies only to Second Generation instances.

fields.name: tier
fields.desc: The tier of service for this instance, for example D1, D2. For more information, see pricing.

fields.name: activationPolicy
fields.desc:
The activation policy specifies when the instance is activated; it is applicable only when the instance state is RUNNABLE. The activation policy cannot be updated together with other settings for Second Generation instances. Valid values:
ALWAYS: The instance is on; it is not deactivated by inactivity.
NEVER: The instance is off; it is not activated, even if a connection request arrives.
ON_DEMAND: The instance responds to incoming requests, and turns itself off when not in use. Instances with PER_USE pricing turn off after 15 minutes of inactivity. Instances with PER_PACKAGE pricing turn off after 12 hours of inactivity.

fields.name: commonName
fields.desc: User supplied name. Must be a distinct name from the other certificates for this instance. New certificates will not be usable until the instance is restarted.

fields.name: items
fields.desc: List of user resources in the instance.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#usersList.

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc: An identifier that uniquely identifies the operation. You can use this identifier to retrieve the Operations resource that has information about the operation.

fields.name: binLogFileName
fields.desc: Name of the binary log file for a Cloud SQL instance.
